NAME

  **pwd** - print working directory


SYNOPSIS

    pwd 

DESCRIPTION

    Pwd (Print Working Directory) will print the path to the current
    working directory. This directory can be changed using cd. No 
    arguments should be passed to pwd.


OPTIONS

  -h, --help:  output usage information and exit

SEE ALSO

    [env](/data/man/env.dsmd), [ls](/data/man/ls.dsmd)